  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your oven to 200°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drizzle the garlic bulbs with a little olive oil and wrap them tightly in foil. Pop them on a baking tray then slide into the oven to roast for 30-35 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, cook the quinoa following packet instructions. Finely slice the fennel (using a mandolin if you have one) and roughly chop the parsley."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Into a large bowl, add the yoghurt and the zest and juice of the lemons along with the squeezed out roasted garlic bulbs. Whisk well and season with salt and pepper. Add the cooked quinoa, fennel and parsley before giving it a good mix."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Enjoy with your choice of protein and carb. If meal prepping for the week, transfer to a container and store in the fridge until ready to eat."
